# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- Using Bit Manipulation to solve it.
- Very easy approach.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- If number is positive calling ans() function and calculating power.
- if number is negative calling ans() function by passing (-n) and returning (1 / ans) as result. [since a ^ -b = 1 / (a ^ b)]
- I am taking care of n = -2147483648 at the begining itself. 😜
- In the ans() function we right shift the value of n until it is 0.
- Everytime x is updated to (x * x) .
- If the last bit of n is 1 then we multiply x to ans.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(logn)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public double myPow(double x, int n) {
        if(x == 1) return 1;
        if(n == -2147483648 && x > 1) return 0;
        if(n >= 0) return ans(x, n);
        else return 1 / ans(x, -1*n);
    }

    double ans(double x,int n){
        double ans = 1;
        while(n > 0){
            if((n & 1) == 1){
                ans *= x;
            }
            x *= x;
            n = n >> 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
