**C++ Solution using bitwise operators**

So the question is that we just need to find the x^n

First we consider teh solution for only positive values of n.

### example pow(3,5)

Our number is 3 and we want 3 raised to teh power 5 . The most basic approach would be to do solmething like 

ans = 3x3x3x3x3 using a for loop but this would be of complexity o(n)

*Optimisation* -> We convert n into its binary form . (ps here n^x means n to the power x and not xor )
* 3^5 =>convert 5 to binary=> 3^(101)
* 3^(101) => 3^(4x1 + 2x0 + 1x1)
*  3^(4x1 + 2x0 + 1x1) =>( 3^(4x1)  ) x (  3^(2x0)  )x ( 3^(1x1))

Here we see a pattern :-
* If we consider n to be in its binary form , then for each set bit in n at index i from the right , we multiply 3 raised to the power of the index value in our answer . And for unset bits we just mutiply ans by 1 or we can skip this.
* What I mean by index value explained ->  The next line will have the binary representaion of a number and below it will have the index value . ex 23
___1____0______1______1_____1
_2^4__2^3 __2^2 __2^1 __2^0
__16____8______4______2_____1

* so if we need the 3^23we just do ans = [3^16] x [1] x [3^4] x [3^2] x  [3^1] . 

### Logic
* Store the vaues of x and n in variables Number and Power respecitively.
* Take an answer variable equal to 1 for now .
* We iterate till our Power is more than 0 . 
* In each iteration => if the last set bit of variable Power is set , the  we multiply our answer with Number. 
* in each itearation => Right shift the power and Square the Number .
* The loop will go through all the bits and multiply teh requires power of n as we have mentioned above .

### Handling for Negative Values of Power
ex 3^(-5)
* We take a bool isNegative and just set it as true if power is negative
* if Power is negative just multily power by -1 and do the same thing as metioned in logic
* Before returning the ans just check if power was negative and if its true , then we return 1/ans
* This is because pow(3,-5) = 1/pow(3/5)

Code 
```
    double myPow(double x, int n) {

        // we store these values 
        double number = x;
        long long power = n ;

        //we just store this bool value to keep a track if our power is negative
        bool isPowerNegative = ( (n<0) ? true : false );
        if( isPowerNegative){
            power= (-1)*power;
        }       
        //how we solve teh qn is that we keep see our power as bbits in binary format
        //if m=3 & n = 5 then => n = 101 >> and 3^5 ==> 3^(bin(101)  ==> 3^(4*1 + 2*0  + 1*1) ==>
        // 3^(4) * 3^(2*0) * 3^(1*1)
        //so at each index of bits , my power of three is swuare and if the bit is set , then
        //we will just multiply that power to our answer
        double answer = 1 ;

        while( power > 0){

            if((power&1) > 0)
            {
                answer *=  number;
            }

            number*=number;
            power = power>>1;

        }

        if(isPowerNegative){
            answer = 1/answer;
        }

        return answer;


    }

