If you have learned the exponential to logarithmic conversion in your school level mathematics. Then, it would be a piece of cake to you.

![solution.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/7f2732bb-de75-41a5-86b9-2d65ed0397b7_1677054064.045268.jpeg)

As the log function accepts only positive value, so we have to check for the negative input.

# Approach
- if x > 0, return the ans as shown in the above image
- if x < 0, first check whether the value of n is even or odd (as for odd the answer would be negative and for even answer will be positve)
for example : $$-2^2 = 4$$ but $$-2^5 = -32$$
- return the answer according to the above logic, see solution for better understanding.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    double myPow(double x, int n) {
        // return the equation, if x > 0
        if (x > 0) return exp(n * log(x));

        // else, we would check for the even and odd parameter
        int sign = n % 2 == 0 ? 1 : -1;
        x = abs(x); // convert the x to positve
        return sign * exp(n * log(x)); // return the result with the appropriate sign
    }
};
```
