# Intuition
Use Stack to store the ans.

# Approach
1) Run a loop over string array tokens.
2) if string equals (*, -, +, /)  perform the claculations popping last two items from the stack and push the ans to the stack.
3) Keep doing until the end of String array.
4) At the end, When the loop is finished, return the top of stack as the ans;


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int evalRPN(String[] tokens) {
        int n = tokens.length;
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();

        for(String s : tokens) {
            if(s.equals("+")) {
                st.push(st.pop() + st.pop());
