# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here, whenever we encounter a number in ```t``` we push it into the stack ```s```  and when we encounter a operator then we pop 2 elements from the stack ```s``` and perform that operation on those 2 operands and push the answer into the stack again for further operations!
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(```n```) [```n``` -> Size of ```t```]
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(```n```) [```n``` -> Number of operands]
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
#define ll long long
class Solution {
public:
    int evalRPN(vector<string>& t) {
        stack<string> s;
        for(int i = 0; i < t.size(); ++i){
            if(t[i] == "+"){
                ll x = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                ll y = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                s.push(to_string(y + x));
            }else
            if(t[i] == "-"){
                ll x = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                ll y = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                s.push(to_string(y - x));
            }else
            if(t[i] == "*"){
                ll x = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                ll y = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                s.push(to_string(y * x));
            }else
            if(t[i] == "/"){
                ll x = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                ll y = stol(s.top()); s.pop();
                s.push(to_string(y / x));
            }else
                s.push(t[i]);
        }

        return stol(s.top());
    }
};
```

