solutions.content:
# Intuition
Analyzing test cases - we can observe a Last In First Out pattern between operands and operators. 

**TEST CASE - 1** 

`["2","1","+","3","*"]`
`((2 + 1) * 3) = 9`

*Iterate the string : -*
- **'2'** -> PUSH
- **'1'** -> PUSH
- **'+'** -> POP top 2 elements *(1 and 2)* perform + operation and push the result into the stack
- **'3'** -> PUSH
- **'*'** -> POP top 2 elements *(3 and result of 2+1)* perform '*' operation and push result into the stack 

**TEST CASE - 2**

`["4","13","5","/","+"]`
`(4 + (13 / 5)) = 6`

*Iterate the string - :*
- **'4'** -> PUSH
- **'13'** -> PUSH
- **'5'** -> PUSH
- **'/'** -> POP top 2 elements of the stack *('5 & 13')* and perform '/' operation on them and push their result into the stack 
- **'+'** -> POP top 2 elements of stack *(result of 13/5 and 4)* and perform '+' operation on them and push their result into the stack

In the end after the entire array has been traversed, the only element in the stack is the result. So, `return stack.top()`

<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Create a stack 
2. Iterate through the given array nums.

> We know, there are only 4 operands '+' '-' '/' '*'
Apart from these operands we only have operands.

3. So, inside the for loop we make **if statements** for operations to be performed **if nums[i] is one of these operators** 
4. **ELSE**, if nums[i] is not any of these operator means **it is a number so we push it into the stack** as a number by using string to integer (stoi) function.

5. In the end, after the entire loop has been traversed the **top element of the stack is the result so we return it** 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int evalRPN(vector<string>&nums) 
    {
        stack<int> s ;
        for(int i = 0 ; i < nums.size() ; i ++)
        {      
            // we know there are only 4 valid operators + - * /

            // if '+' , add top two elements of stack
            if(nums[i] == "+")
            {
                int x = s.top(); 
                s.pop();
                int y = s.top(); 
                s.pop();

                s.push(x + y) ;
            }

            // if '-' , subtract top two elements of stack
            else if(nums[i] == "-")
            {
                int x = s.top() ; 
                s.pop();
                int y = s.top() ; 
                s.pop();

                s.push(y - x) ;
            }

            // if '*' , multiply top two elements of stack
            else if(nums[i] == "*")
            {
                int x = s.top() ; 
                s.pop() ;
                int y = s.top() ; 
                s.pop() ;

                s.push(y * x) ;
            }

            // if '/' , divide top two elements of stack
            else if(nums[i] == "/")
            {
                int x = s.top() ; 
                s.pop() ;
                int y = s.top() ; 
                s.pop() ;

                s.push(y / x) ;
            }

            // if nums[i] is a character push into the stack 
            else
            {
                s.push(stoi(nums[i])) ;
            }
        }
        return s.top() ;
    }
};
```
