# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
iterate the whole tokens array,and check for each element
now if the element is not "+" or "-" or "/" or "*" 
then it means the element is a digit so we push the element by converting it into an integer in the stack
now whenever we encounter any "+" or "-" or "/" or "*" operation
then we pop the top 2 elements from the stack and perform the operation the the 2 elements
after preforming operation storing the result of the operation in the top of the stack and keep iterating the tokens array
at the en the element at the top of the array is the required answer

NOTE: we used long long to avoid overflow

example:
4,13,5,/,+
stack: empty

STEP I

we encounter 4 so we push it in the stack
stack: {4}

STEP II

we encounter 13 so we push it in the stack
stack: {4,13}

STEP III

we encounter 5 so we push it in the stack
stack: {4,13,5}

STEP IV

we encounter / so we pop top 2 elements from the stack i.e. 13,5
stack: {4}
ans =round to lowest integer(13/5)=2
and then push 2 in the stack
stack: {4,2}

STEP V

we encounter + so we pop top 2 elements from the stack i.e. 4,2
stack: empty
ans =round to lowest integer(4+2)=6
and then push 6 in the stack
stack: {6}

STEP VI

now the top of the stack is our answer :)


