solutions.content:
The `tokens` vector represents the post-order traversal of a binary tree where each sub-tree represents a sub-expression of the overall expression. Every node that has an operator value (*, /, +, -) must have left and right children. Every node that has a numeric value must be a leaf.

The last element of `tokens` is the root of the tree and the previous element in `tokens` is the root of the right subtree. Therefore we can start at the end of `tokens` and evaluate each subtree recursively. The base case is when the current element is a number and not an operator (*, /, +, -). The variable `currIdx` is used to keep track of where we are in the tree so we can know where a given left sub-tree starts.

**Time complexity: O(n)** because we are traversing every node of the tree (every element of `tokens`)
**Space complexity: O(n)** because each recursive call adds memory on the stack. In the worst case, the tree is one-sided and has a depth of n.

This problem can also be solved iteratively by iterating from the start of `tokens` and using a stack. That approach will have the same time and space complextiy.


```
class Solution {
public:

    // helper function that returns true if input is a valid operator, false otherwise
    bool isoperator(const string& s) {
        if (s.compare("*") == 0) return true;
        if (s.compare("/") == 0) return true;
        if (s.compare("+") == 0) return true;
        if (s.compare("-") == 0) return true;
        return false;
    }

    // recursive helper evalRPN
    int evalRPN(vector<string>& tokens, int& currIdx) {
        // base case: if current value is a number it's a leaf node, return value and increment expression length
        string currVal = tokens[currIdx--];
        if (!isoperator(currVal)) return stoi(currVal);

        // evaluate right subtree
        int right = evalRPN(tokens, currIdx);

        // evaluate left subtree
        int left = evalRPN(tokens, currIdx);

        // return left (operator) right
        if (currVal == "*") return left * right;
        if (currVal == "/") return left / right;
        if (currVal == "+") return left + right;
        if (currVal == "-") return left - right;

        return 0;   // invalid operator
    }

    int evalRPN(vector<string>& tokens) {
        if (tokens.empty()) return 0;

        // start at end of tokens (root of expression)
        int currIdx = tokens.size() - 1;
        return evalRPN(tokens, currIdx);
    }
};
```

