## Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Maintain a stack of integers. Iterate through the ```tokens``` vector :
- If```tokens[i]```is an integer (where```i```is the iterator), push```tokens[i]```to the stack.

- If```tokens[i]```is an arithmetic operation, the top two numbers in the stack are popped; the concerned arithmetic operation is applied to the two numbers and the result of the operation is pushed back to the stack. Pushing the result simulates the use of brackets, i.e. evaluating the results in order of the brackets in the combined arithmetic operation.
(*For operations in which order of integers matters, i.e. subtraction and division, the integer popped second from the stack is the one to be considered first in the order, and the one popped first is to be considered second in the order.*)


## Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
#include <string>
class Solution {
public:
    int evalRPN(vector<string>& tokens) {
        stack<int> s;

        for(int i=0; i<tokens.size(); i++){
            string x = tokens[i];

            if(x=="+"){
                int a = s.top();
                s.pop();
                int b = s.top();
                s.pop();
                s.push(a+b);
            }
            else if(x=="-"){
                int a = s.top();
                s.pop();
                int b = s.top();
                s.pop();
                s.push(b-a);
            }
            else if(x=="*"){
                int a = s.top();
                s.pop();
                int b = s.top();
                s.pop();
                s.push(a*b);
            }
            else if(x=="/"){
                int a = s.top();
                s.pop();
                int b = s.top();
                s.pop();
                s.push(b/a);
            }
            else{
                s.push(stoi(x));
            }
        }

        return s.top();
    }
};
```

