# Intuition :
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to return the intersection of two arrays, i.e. all the common elements that these both arrays share.
This problem can be  solved through simple comparison using two pointer approach.

# Approach :
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
To begin solving the problem we'll first sort both the arrays to make future comparisons.
then we'll place two pointers each at the strating of the two arrays to make the final comparisons and we'll store the final result in the array ans.
# Complexity :
- Time complexity: nearly $$O(n*log(n))$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity : No extra space was used so $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->



