# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Intuition is to use a frequency array seeing the constraints. The max size of any array element is <=1000 that means a frequency array occupying not much space. And the traversing the array also becomes time-efficient due to the small constraints.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Approach:
- First traverse both arrays and store the frequency of their elements in respective freq[] arrays of sizes 1001 each (since constraint is at 1000). 
- Next, traverse and integer i from 0 to 1001 in a resulting frequency array freqres[] which is also of the size 1001.
     - At each iteration do the operation: freqres[i] = Math.min(freq1[i], freq2[i])
     - Also, keep track of the sum of the values of the freqres array in a variable "size", as this will be the size of the final array res[].
- Next, intitialize a pointer as 0 and start traversal of the freqres[] array, where for each non-zero element of freqres[]:
    - Keep decrementing the freqres[i] until zero
    - and for each decrementing iteration, keep incrementing the pointer 
    - while storing "i" in res[pointer] where, res[] is the resulting array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
    - Since we can have larger constraints, the time complexity will depend on number of same elements and the range of elements. Which is **O(n+k)**, where n is max(nums1.length, nums2,length), and k is the range of data.


- Space complexity:
    - In terms of 'n' and 'k', it will be **O(n+k)** as well.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] intersect(int[] nums1, int[] nums2) {
        int freq1[] = new int[1001];
        int freq2[] = new int[1001];
        for(int i=0;i<nums1.length;i++){
            freq1[nums1[i]]++;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<nums2.length;i++){
            freq2[nums2[i]]++;
        }
        int freqres[] = new int[1001];
        int size=0;
        for(int i=0;i<1001;i++){
            freqres[i] = Math.min(freq1[i],freq2[i]);
            size+=freqres[i];
        }
        int res[] = new int[size];
        int pointer = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<1001;i++){
            while(freqres[i]!=0){
                res[pointer] = i;
                pointer++;
                freqres[i]--;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

